 context, third-party support had absolutely cratered on Wii U, so the company needed to convey that partners were on board with Switch. However, it would have been nice for Nintendo to give third parties the option to tease their games with Switch 2 instead of only vague Mario Kart footage. Showing that Fortnite will, in fact, work on Switch 2 seems like a no-brainer and easy win.</p><div tabindex="0" data-id="77104904" data-promo-id="0" data-user-has-ads="1" data-video="{&quot;id&quot;:6435273,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Nintendo%20Switch%20-%20Reveal%20Trailer&quot;,&quot;lengthSeconds&quot;:217,&quot;startTime&quot;:0,&quot;autoplay&quot;:false,&quot;share&quot;:{&quot;linkUrl&quot;:&quot;https://www.gamespot.com/videos/nintendo-switch-reveal-trailer/2300-6435273/&quot;,&quot;embedUrl&quot;:&quot;https://www.gamespot.com/videos/embed/6435273/&quot;,&quot;embedHtml&quot;:{&quot;640&quot;:&quot;









